From 0b8c8f858a7e327003c499edd3b8f99ca670d22c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 17:41:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add 1-click GCP Connect via shared service account + IAM
 grant
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Third and final cloud provider for Brownfield auto-discover.
Simpler than both AWS and Azure — no CloudFormation stack, no OAuth
redirect. ArchAI has one service account; customers just grant it
Viewer in their project's IAM, matching the trust model of AWS's
cross-account role but with even less setup.

- lib/gcp-connect/auth.ts: getServiceAccountEmail() (parsed from
  ArchAI's own key JSON, shown to customers so they know exactly
  what to grant access to) and getAccessToken() via google-auth-library's
  GoogleAuth, scoped read-only.
- lib/gcp-connect/scanner.ts: discovery via direct REST calls
  (Compute, Storage, Cloud SQL Admin APIs) using the acquired
  token. Same resource types/properties as archai-cli's GCP
  provider. Untested against a real GCP project (same honest
  caveat as Azure) — written against the documented REST API
  surface, not yet live-verified.
- app/api/gcp-connect/info: returns the service account email for
  display.
- app/api/gcp-connect/verify: attempts a real Compute API call to
  confirm Viewer was actually granted (auth succeeding alone proves
  nothing, same lesson learned from AWS/Azure). No separate 'init'
  step needed since there's no stack/consent flow to kick off first
  — verify both confirms access AND creates the connection row in
  one step.
- app/api/gcp-connect/scan: same pipeline as every other Brownfield
  entry point, including the zero-resources guard from the start
  this time (learned from the Azure empty-subscription incident).
- app/api/gcp-connect/status: existing-connection check, same
  'connect once, scan many times' pattern as AWS/Azure.
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldClient.tsx: new 'Connect GCP
  (1-click)' option — single-screen flow (grant access, enter
  Project ID, verify), no multi-step redirect handling needed.
- package.json: added google-auth-library, @google-cloud/compute,
  @google-cloud/storage, googleapis (all verified real, current
  versions against npm).

Needs before this works in production:
1. Run create_gcp_connections_table.sql in Supabase.
2. Set ARCHAI_GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY in Vercel — the full JSON key
   file content for ArchAI's own GCP service account, pasted as-is.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (4 new
gcp-connect routes confirmed), no new lint errors beyond the one
pre-existing no-html-link-for-pages issue.
